caption: The image illustrates a bar magnet oriented within a uniform magnetic field represented by dashed arrows labeled 'B'. The north pole (N) and south pole (S) of the magnet are clearly marked, along with the angle θ between the direction of the magnetic field and the axis of the magnet. This setup is commonly used to explain the torque experienced by a magnet in a magnetic field.
key_elements: Bar magnet with poles labeled N and S
Uniform magnetic field lines represented by dashed arrows
Angle θ between the magnet's axis and the magnetic field
scientific_context: This diagram is relevant in electromagnetism, specifically in understanding how a bar magnet interacts with an external magnetic field. It helps in explaining the principles behind the behavior of magnetic dipoles in magnetic fields, which is fundamental in various applications such as electric motors and magnetic storage devices.
